1
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:36,911
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:01:05,189 --> 00:01:07,233
Are you here for a blind date?

3
00:01:10,736 --> 00:01:11,779
No, I'm not.

4
00:01:12,405 --> 00:01:13,406
Sorry.

5
00:01:13,489 --> 00:01:14,490
Ui-yeong!

6
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:15,866
- Hey!
- Over here!

7
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:17,493
It's been a minute.

8
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:19,495
- Seriously!
- You look stunning.

9
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:20,580
- Me?
- Yeah.

10
00:01:20,663 --> 00:01:21,914
- Beautiful.
- You're glowing!

11
00:01:22,623 --> 00:01:23,708
Thanks.

12
00:01:24,709 --> 00:01:26,294
- How's everyone doing?
- Well.

13
00:01:26,377 --> 00:01:27,420
- It's been so long.
- Yeah.

14
00:01:27,503 --> 00:01:28,796
- Everyone's busy.
- We only meet

15
00:01:28,879 --> 00:01:30,006
- when someone's getting married.
- I know.

16
00:01:30,089 --> 00:01:31,424
- Seriously.
- Life gets busy.

17
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,968
How have you been?

18
00:01:36,345 --> 00:01:38,014
- Thank you.
- My, my.

19
00:01:38,097 --> 00:01:39,307
- Please come.
- Will do!

20
00:01:40,349 --> 00:01:41,475
- My gosh.
- Is it okay?

21
00:01:41,559 --> 00:01:42,560
- Yeah.
- Of course!

22
00:01:42,643 --> 00:01:43,978
It's so pretty and neat.

23
00:01:44,061 --> 00:01:45,771
- Beautiful.
- It was a lot of work.

24
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:47,690
I can't believe you're getting married.

25
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:52,403
It feels like just yesterday
when you booked the venue. Time flies.

26
00:01:52,486 --> 00:01:54,322
- I know.
- Congrats.

27
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,531
You must be so busy.

28
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:56,824
Yeah, it's crazy.

29
00:01:56,907 --> 00:01:57,950
I have to invite people

30
00:01:58,034 --> 00:01:59,869
plan the wedding, and move.

31
00:02:00,202 --> 00:02:02,830
I'm even getting
a wedding check-up next week.

32
00:02:03,247 --> 00:02:04,248
A wedding check-up?

33
00:02:04,332 --> 00:02:05,583
It's just what they call it.

34
00:02:05,666 --> 00:02:07,960
They visit a gynecologist and a urologist

35
00:02:08,044 --> 00:02:09,670
to make sure they're fertile.

36
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:12,089
Is that common these days?

37
00:02:12,173 --> 00:02:13,215
Yeah.

38
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:15,843
But there are some fun things to do
along the way.

39
00:02:15,926 --> 00:02:16,969
Like what?

40
00:02:17,345 --> 00:02:18,471
Ta-da!

41
00:02:18,804 --> 00:02:21,140
- No way!
- That's beautiful!

42
00:02:21,223 --> 00:02:23,684
It's so pretty and sparkly!

43
00:02:23,851 --> 00:02:25,144
That's crazy, isn't it?

44
00:02:25,227 --> 00:02:27,480
Look at Ui-yeong getting excited
after seeing that.

45
00:02:27,563 --> 00:02:28,564
I know!

46
00:02:28,648 --> 00:02:30,816
That's a big rock.
I've never seen one that big.

47
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:32,526
Isn't it heavy to wear?

48
00:02:32,610 --> 00:02:33,819
- It's too heavy.
- Right?

49
00:02:33,903 --> 00:02:35,196
- Put it down.
- My gosh.

50
00:02:35,279 --> 00:02:36,697
You're so funny.

51
00:02:37,323 --> 00:02:39,075
When are you getting married?

52
00:02:39,158 --> 00:02:40,159
- Me?
- Yeah.

53
00:02:40,242 --> 00:02:42,411
You're the only single one left
once I get married.

54
00:02:42,662 --> 00:02:44,622
Oh, you're right.

55
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:49,543
Is your current boyfriend
not really husband material?

56
00:02:49,627 --> 00:02:51,379
No, he's great.

57
00:02:51,462 --> 00:02:52,505
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

58
00:02:52,588 --> 00:02:54,256
I just don't want to get married yet.

59
00:02:56,133 --> 00:02:58,469
By the way

60
00:02:58,552 --> 00:03:01,681
was there a moment
when you realized you knew he was the one?

61
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:05,142
Yeah, I was just eating with him one day

62
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:09,438
and realized we'd probably eat together
for the rest of our lives.

63
00:03:09,647 --> 00:03:10,648
What about you?

64
00:03:10,731 --> 00:03:12,525
When I got pregnant.

65
00:03:13,401 --> 00:03:17,196
Seeing him step up and tell our parents
about our pregnancy

66
00:03:17,279 --> 00:03:18,531
I knew I could trust him.

67
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:21,492
Is it really necessary to be so dramatic?

68
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:24,787
Aren't you bound to marry
whomever you're dating around this age?

69
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,666
Bring your boyfriend to the wedding.
We'll see what he's like.

70
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:31,001
Yeah, we're curious.

71
00:03:32,169 --> 00:03:34,130
Okay, I'll ask him if he's free.

72
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:37,091
Oh, right!

73
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,009
- Ui-yeong!
- Yeah?

74
00:03:39,093 --> 00:03:41,220
Could you give the wedding toast?

75
00:03:41,303 --> 00:03:43,180
- Me? No way.
- Yeah.

76
00:03:43,264 --> 00:03:46,600
Why not? You were always good
at public speaking.

77
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:48,519
- Yeah.
- Come on.

78
00:03:48,602 --> 00:03:50,730
I did that for good grades.

79
00:03:50,855 --> 00:03:52,606
I'm not even married. What do I even say?

80
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:56,402
I'd hate to get nervous and even tear up

81
00:03:56,485 --> 00:03:58,654
before the person
even begins their speech.

82
00:03:58,904 --> 00:04:00,322
I can't stand that.

83
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:01,782
Come on, I can't do it.

84
00:04:01,866 --> 00:04:04,535
Just take it easy and keep it simple.

85
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:06,078
- Yeah.
- Just say nice things.

86
00:04:06,162 --> 00:04:08,330
- Help her.
- Yeah, help her out.

87
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:09,874
- Yeah.
- She's begging you.

88
00:04:11,250 --> 00:04:12,251
Fine.

89
00:04:12,668 --> 00:04:14,044
- Really?
- Yeah.

90
00:04:14,295 --> 00:04:16,255
Yes! I got my wedding toast!

91
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:17,673
Keep it simple, okay?

92
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:19,049
Simple. Not too emotional.

93
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:20,134
Don't cry, okay?

94
00:04:20,217 --> 00:04:21,385
- You too!
- Yeah, you!

95
00:04:23,679 --> 00:04:26,265
How would you like to renovate
your workshop?

96
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:30,394
A lot of customers want to visit
to buy my products

97
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:33,689
so I'd like to have a showroom with it,
even if it's small.

98
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:35,483
But the space is already tiny.

99
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:37,985
Could I take some photos?

100
00:04:38,068 --> 00:04:39,069
Of course.

101
00:04:39,361 --> 00:04:42,281
We'll have space to work with
once we add cabinets

102
00:04:42,364 --> 00:04:44,158
- along the ceiling.
- I see.

103
00:04:44,241 --> 00:04:46,452
Is there a specific design you want?

104
00:04:46,535 --> 00:04:47,745
Well, actually...

105
00:04:48,078 --> 00:04:50,956
I chose you as my designer
after seeing your work at the exhibition.

106
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,209
- I see.
- I want a design

107
00:04:53,292 --> 00:04:55,920
that's timelessly beautiful
instead of just trendy.

108
00:04:56,128 --> 00:04:57,379
Okay, then.

109
00:04:57,463 --> 00:04:58,464
Thank you.

110
00:05:00,090 --> 00:05:02,843
Did you make this yourself, too?

111
00:05:02,927 --> 00:05:03,969
Yeah.

112
00:05:06,806 --> 00:05:08,808
Wow, that's stunning.

113
00:05:10,851 --> 00:05:14,188
I bet couples who wear these rings
will never run out of love.

114
00:05:15,105 --> 00:05:17,024
You think so? Maybe that's why.

115
00:05:17,316 --> 00:05:19,819
Every couple with those rings got married.

116
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:21,403
- Really?
- Yeah.

117
00:05:22,363 --> 00:05:25,699
But I'm not going to make more of them
because I don't want to break the record.

118
00:05:25,783 --> 00:05:28,244
I'm only going to make custom rings
from now on.

119
00:05:28,327 --> 00:05:30,120
I see.

120
00:05:31,914 --> 00:05:33,582
Would you like to see the inside?

121
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:34,667
Sure.

122
00:05:39,797 --> 00:05:42,258
YOU ARE CORDIALLY INVITED
TO HO-JIN AND EUN-MI'S WEDDING

123
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:49,849
Hey, Ui-yeong.

124
00:05:50,516 --> 00:05:51,517
Hey.

125
00:05:52,601 --> 00:05:53,602
Aren't you hungry?

126
00:05:53,686 --> 00:05:55,646
I wanted to eat with you, so I barely ate.

127
00:05:55,729 --> 00:05:56,939
I barely had any!

128
00:05:57,106 --> 00:05:58,107
Good job.

129
00:05:58,190 --> 00:05:59,191
- Let's go.
- I'm so hungry.

130
00:06:00,568 --> 00:06:01,694
It's going to be so good!

131
00:06:08,450 --> 00:06:09,535
It looks amazing.

132
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,710
- Here. Have this.
- Thanks.

133
00:06:22,214 --> 00:06:23,507
This looks amazing.

134
00:06:23,591 --> 00:06:24,675
Try it.

135
00:06:32,391 --> 00:06:33,642
The sauce is so good.

136
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:34,852
- Right?
- Yeah.

137
00:06:35,144 --> 00:06:38,230
Your restaurant recommendations
never disappoint.

138
00:06:38,772 --> 00:06:39,773
I knew you'd love it.

139
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:42,860
This simple flavor could make
anyone's day.

140
00:06:43,527 --> 00:06:45,905
Oh, did you have fun with your friends?

141
00:06:46,322 --> 00:06:48,741
Yeah, we talked so much.

142
00:06:49,283 --> 00:06:52,286
Oh, and they're dying to meet you.

143
00:06:52,369 --> 00:06:53,746
They want you at the wedding.

144
00:06:54,079 --> 00:06:55,456
I can go. I'll make time.

145
00:06:55,539 --> 00:06:57,124
- Really?
- Yeah.

146
00:06:58,709 --> 00:07:02,504
I get invited to a wedding
or have a wedding to attend every week.

147
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:04,381
There's no time to go on dates

148
00:07:04,465 --> 00:07:07,009
because I'm too busy
celebrating other people's love.

149
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:10,763
Your friends

150
00:07:11,347 --> 00:07:14,600
also always talk
about getting married, right?

151
00:07:16,268 --> 00:07:17,519
Yeah, I guess so.

152
00:07:17,728 --> 00:07:20,564
Before that, it was about our careers

153
00:07:20,648 --> 00:07:22,274
and how much we were making.

154
00:07:22,358 --> 00:07:24,026
That was what everyone cared about

155
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:27,821
but now, it's about getting married
and buying a new house.

156
00:07:29,531 --> 00:07:32,159
I guess it's natural for everyone
to become that way.

157
00:07:33,410 --> 00:07:37,206
It can be natural for some,
but unnatural for others.

158
00:07:37,581 --> 00:07:39,208
Everyone has a different pace in life.

159
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:41,210
That's true.

160
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:44,004
Oh, are you free tomorrow?

161
00:07:44,088 --> 00:07:45,714
I want to bring you the chair.

162
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:48,926
Oh, really? It's finally coming!

163
00:07:49,009 --> 00:07:50,803
I'm so excited. I can't wait to sit in it.

164
00:07:51,887 --> 00:07:53,472
- I'll bring it tomorrow.
- Perfect.

165
00:08:03,941 --> 00:08:05,526
- No, wait!
- What?

166
00:08:05,609 --> 00:08:06,860
Not this one.

167
00:08:06,944 --> 00:08:08,529
This is my trophy.

168
00:08:08,612 --> 00:08:10,322
Trophy, my ass. It's whiskey.

169
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:11,448
No!

170
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:13,742
It's from my supervisor after I exceeded

171
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:15,244
the sales goal by 100%.

172
00:08:15,327 --> 00:08:16,537
No!

173
00:08:16,996 --> 00:08:18,539
Come on.

174
00:08:18,622 --> 00:08:21,166
Let's just leave it as a token
of my past glory.

175
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:22,960
Didn't you hear the doctor?

176
00:08:23,043 --> 00:08:25,504
It's on you
for leaving it unopened all this time.

177
00:08:25,963 --> 00:08:30,092
Why don't we start drinking tea
instead of alcohol now?

178
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:32,011
The world of tea seems just as serious

179
00:08:32,094 --> 00:08:34,221
from what I saw during my tea field visit.

180
00:08:34,304 --> 00:08:36,015
Drink white tea instead of white wine

181
00:08:36,098 --> 00:08:37,683
and black tea instead of red, okay?

182
00:08:37,766 --> 00:08:39,101
What are you talking about?

183
00:08:39,184 --> 00:08:40,227
Great, right?

184
00:08:40,352 --> 00:08:41,395
Even today?

185
00:08:41,478 --> 00:08:43,647
Of course! You're ridiculous.

186
00:08:51,780 --> 00:08:53,449
It's so comfortable!

187
00:08:53,532 --> 00:08:54,867
- Is it?
- Yeah, even the back!

188
00:08:55,075 --> 00:08:57,411
How did you build this? I love it.

189
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,121
I'm glad.

190
00:08:59,496 --> 00:09:01,874
And doesn't it fit right in at my house?

191
00:09:01,957 --> 00:09:04,043
- Yeah, it does.
- Thank you!

192
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:07,379
Have some tea if you're done.

193
00:09:07,463 --> 00:09:08,505
- Okay.
- Yes, ma'am.

194
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:09,590
Come.

195
00:09:13,093 --> 00:09:14,261
It smells so nice.

196
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:17,264
Is it okay?

197
00:09:17,431 --> 00:09:18,807
I love it.

198
00:09:21,351 --> 00:09:25,898
So, you build and sell furniture
like the chair?

199
00:09:25,981 --> 00:09:27,524
Yeah, I build furniture

200
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:30,027
and also get clients
from architectural firms and brands

201
00:09:30,110 --> 00:09:32,321
to design spaces.

202
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:35,616
You're definitely not car poor, then.

203
00:09:35,699 --> 00:09:36,784
- Mom!
- Hmm?

204
00:09:37,284 --> 00:09:38,869
Hmm? Oh, it's nothing.

205
00:09:39,578 --> 00:09:41,205
Do you have any goals?

206
00:09:41,288 --> 00:09:43,165
Why are you asking him that?

207
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:44,708
Do you have any goals?

208
00:09:44,958 --> 00:09:46,794
Not anymore

209
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:48,212
but I did when I was your age.

210
00:09:48,378 --> 00:09:50,380
Supporting you until you enter college.

211
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:57,387
In my twenties, I was more focused
on proving myself professionally

212
00:09:57,763 --> 00:09:59,264
but work isn't my focus anymore.

213
00:09:59,348 --> 00:10:03,769
Now, spending time with Ui-yeong,
my family, and colleagues is the best.

214
00:10:03,852 --> 00:10:05,187
I feel alive.

215
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:08,440
Being together with my loved ones
for a long time is

216
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:10,109
my new goal, I guess.

217
00:10:10,192 --> 00:10:11,193
I see.

218
00:10:11,401 --> 00:10:12,903
So, you know what's important.

219
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:16,782
My last and biggest question is...

220
00:10:16,865 --> 00:10:18,450
Mom! Cut it out.

221
00:10:18,534 --> 00:10:20,494
What do you love so much about Ui-yeong?

222
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:23,247
Yeah, I'm kind of curious, too.

223
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:27,501
At first, I was drawn to her beauty.

224
00:10:27,584 --> 00:10:28,919
You hear that?

225
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:31,171
I love
how we just understand each other, too.

226
00:10:31,421 --> 00:10:33,048
And now that I know her better

227
00:10:33,132 --> 00:10:35,634
I also love her honesty
and unpredictable personality.

228
00:10:36,051 --> 00:10:38,679
I found all those things attractive.

229
00:10:39,429 --> 00:10:41,348
I'm calm and logical

230
00:10:41,431 --> 00:10:42,933
but when I'm with Ui-yeong

231
00:10:43,183 --> 00:10:46,228
I become more emotional
and motivated to take initiatives.

232
00:10:46,728 --> 00:10:50,649
I'm thinking maybe that's what love is...

233
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:54,069
Sorry.

234
00:10:54,903 --> 00:10:56,530
You taught me love right there.

235
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:02,286
Are you getting shy
after that perfect answer?

236
00:11:02,369 --> 00:11:03,954
You're as red as an apple.

237
00:11:05,414 --> 00:11:06,415
It's hot!

238
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:09,334
- I need to use the bathroom.
- That way.

239
00:11:11,378 --> 00:11:12,462
My gosh.

240
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:14,715
- Isn't he cute?
- Love?

241
00:11:14,798 --> 00:11:16,091
I'm definitely loved.

242
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:17,801
That's very cute.

243
00:11:17,885 --> 00:11:19,261
- Jealous?
- Yeah.

244
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:22,472
I'll turn the light on.

245
00:11:27,102 --> 00:11:28,520
Let's see.

246
00:11:29,229 --> 00:11:30,355
First

247
00:11:30,856 --> 00:11:31,857
bell peppers.

248
00:11:32,482 --> 00:11:33,483
Sweet potatoes.

249
00:11:35,694 --> 00:11:37,905
Three tomatoes.

250
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:43,744
Three big sweet potatoes.

251
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:46,914
And three potatoes!

252
00:11:47,831 --> 00:11:49,333
Wait, Jun!

253
00:11:49,416 --> 00:11:50,542
I don't need all this.

254
00:11:51,668 --> 00:11:52,753
You can take more.

255
00:11:52,836 --> 00:11:54,504
You're much bigger than me.

256
00:11:55,547 --> 00:11:57,174
But we split the bill equally.

257
00:11:57,716 --> 00:11:59,092
No.

258
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:03,096
I just don't think I can finish them
before they go bad.

259
00:12:03,388 --> 00:12:05,349
It's better for you to enjoy it all

260
00:12:05,432 --> 00:12:07,184
instead of having some go bad.

261
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:10,145
And I already got my money's worth
by splitting the bill.

262
00:12:10,312 --> 00:12:12,856
This is better
than splitting everything evenly.

263
00:12:14,107 --> 00:12:16,109
How are you so kind, too?

264
00:12:17,027 --> 00:12:18,028
Okay, then.

265
00:12:18,862 --> 00:12:20,822
Since you like this

266
00:12:22,032 --> 00:12:23,075
you can take three!

267
00:12:25,577 --> 00:12:27,996
How do you already know
what I love so well?

268
00:12:33,418 --> 00:12:35,921
LANDLORD

269
00:12:37,756 --> 00:12:38,799
What's wrong?

270
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:42,469
- Excuse me for a sec.
- Okay.

271
00:12:44,096 --> 00:12:46,890
Hello, sir. I'm Seung-jun.

272
00:12:49,309 --> 00:12:50,352
Sorry?

273
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:53,855
MONTHLY EXPENSES

274
00:12:54,648 --> 00:12:56,525
How can they raise the rent again?

275
00:12:57,109 --> 00:12:59,319
It's not like I can stop using
the AC and the heater.

276
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:01,989
Should I sell a machine?

277
00:13:03,323 --> 00:13:05,325
You'll end up with an empty gym

278
00:13:05,409 --> 00:13:07,202
if you sell one every time this happens.

279
00:13:07,744 --> 00:13:08,787
Let me see.

280
00:13:09,454 --> 00:13:10,956
FIXED EXPENSES

281
00:13:11,039 --> 00:13:14,835
Was I too ambitious for opening a gym
on the first floor with a good view?

282
00:13:17,087 --> 00:13:18,880
I should've started in a semi-basement.

283
00:13:23,510 --> 00:13:26,138
You're already doing everything you can.

284
00:13:27,973 --> 00:13:29,349
Why don't you move the gym?

285
00:13:31,601 --> 00:13:34,813
All the money I spent on renovations
would go to waste.

286
00:13:36,148 --> 00:13:38,942
And there's no guarantee
that my customers will move with me.

287
00:13:57,627 --> 00:13:59,129
You could save on one more thing.

288
00:13:59,212 --> 00:14:00,213
Huh?

289
00:14:00,964 --> 00:14:02,257
- And that's enough?
- Yeah.

290
00:14:02,632 --> 00:14:03,717
This unit.

291
00:14:04,176 --> 00:14:06,970
Move out of this unit and move in with me.

292
00:14:08,305 --> 00:14:09,848
- Huh?
- Jun.

293
00:14:14,728 --> 00:14:16,104
Will you be my house husband?

294
00:14:31,411 --> 00:14:32,954
You're not asleep yet?

295
00:14:33,038 --> 00:14:34,915
- Oh, yeah...
- What's that?

296
00:14:35,540 --> 00:14:37,084
Don't tell me you're working.

297
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:39,127
The doctor said
you shouldn't work too hard.

298
00:14:39,211 --> 00:14:40,796
That's not it.

299
00:14:41,588 --> 00:14:43,840
- Can we talk for a sec?
- Oh, sure.

300
00:14:56,686 --> 00:14:59,648
CONFIRMATION OF APPLICATION
FOR AN UNCONTESTED DIVORCE

301
00:15:01,358 --> 00:15:03,944
One of my clients once said

302
00:15:04,236 --> 00:15:05,570
experiencing falling ill

303
00:15:05,987 --> 00:15:08,073
isn't entirely a bad thing.

304
00:15:08,657 --> 00:15:11,243
I didn't understand her then

305
00:15:12,202 --> 00:15:13,954
but I get it now.

306
00:15:14,621 --> 00:15:15,789
I now understand

307
00:15:16,289 --> 00:15:19,251
what to keep and get rid of in my life.

308
00:15:20,043 --> 00:15:21,086
So

309
00:15:23,547 --> 00:15:26,508
if you're okay,
I want to go forward with this.

310
00:15:30,595 --> 00:15:31,638
Mom

311
00:15:32,681 --> 00:15:34,141
it's your life.

312
00:15:34,224 --> 00:15:36,643
You need to go for it
if that's what you want.

313
00:15:38,353 --> 00:15:40,313
I don't want to hold you back, ever.

314
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:42,399
I want to support you in everything.

315
00:15:44,192 --> 00:15:45,444
Like you did today

316
00:15:47,362 --> 00:15:48,572
I want you

317
00:15:49,364 --> 00:15:53,452
to keep prioritizing yourself
over anything and anyone.

318
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:57,581
I'll feel really happy, then.

319
00:16:00,917 --> 00:16:01,960
Seriously

320
00:16:03,086 --> 00:16:05,172
when did my little girl grow up?

321
00:16:06,965 --> 00:16:08,550
You raised me.

322
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:11,595
My gosh.

323
00:16:14,055 --> 00:16:15,640
- Okay, let's do this.
- Yeah.

324
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:21,354
CONFIRMATION OF APPLICATION
FOR AN UNCONTESTED DIVORCE

325
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:27,527
PARK JEONG-IM

326
00:16:39,414 --> 00:16:42,167
STUDIO HOME

327
00:16:42,250 --> 00:16:43,752
Check this out, Sae-byeok.

328
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:46,588
He's a close friend of mine.

329
00:16:47,130 --> 00:16:48,715
He's handsome.

330
00:16:49,132 --> 00:16:50,425
He's also a great guy.

331
00:16:51,134 --> 00:16:52,135
What do you think?

332
00:16:52,302 --> 00:16:53,428
You want me to set you up?

333
00:16:55,972 --> 00:16:57,933
- What?
- There he goes again!

334
00:17:00,101 --> 00:17:01,436
Are you okay?

335
00:17:01,645 --> 00:17:04,105
- That was loud. Are you hurt?
- What's going on?

336
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:06,441
I'm fine, babe. Don't be...

337
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:11,488
What's going on?

338
00:17:11,571 --> 00:17:14,324
This is huge.

339
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:20,330
My gosh.

340
00:17:20,664 --> 00:17:24,125
I thought we were a family,
but we have lovebirds now.

341
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:26,378
I know. How dare they?

342
00:17:26,461 --> 00:17:28,421
You said you didn't date coworkers,
Sae-byeok.

343
00:17:28,505 --> 00:17:31,091
Yeah, and I meant it back then.

344
00:17:32,259 --> 00:17:34,427
That was just months ago.

345
00:17:34,761 --> 00:17:36,721
It's still 2026, you know?

346
00:17:36,888 --> 00:17:39,057
It's all because of you, Mr. Song.

347
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:41,142
- What?
- Hmm? What did I do?

348
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:42,852
It's all thanks to you.

349
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:46,565
You kept leaving us by ourselves
to go on dates with your girlfriend.

350
00:17:46,773 --> 00:17:48,942
I have plans. You two can go.

351
00:17:49,025 --> 00:17:50,026
Good work.

352
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:51,361
- You too.
- Thank you.

353
00:17:52,195 --> 00:17:53,196
So...

354
00:17:54,864 --> 00:17:56,032
you want to grab dinner?

355
00:17:57,284 --> 00:17:58,285
Okay.

356
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:00,370
- It's hot. Be careful.
- Okay.

357
00:18:04,874 --> 00:18:05,875
What are you doing?

358
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,669
This is Ui-yeong's tip.

359
00:18:07,752 --> 00:18:10,046
This way, you can eat quickly
without burning yourself.

360
00:18:15,385 --> 00:18:16,886
Gosh, you little piggy.

361
00:18:18,763 --> 00:18:19,764
She's so cute.

362
00:18:22,851 --> 00:18:24,019
- Like this?
- Yeah.

363
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:32,277
I got this.

364
00:18:36,323 --> 00:18:38,283
It doesn't move when you even it out.

365
00:18:39,743 --> 00:18:40,785
See? It's stable.

366
00:18:44,706 --> 00:18:45,957
He's so cool.

367
00:18:49,252 --> 00:18:53,131
We won't let our relationship
affect our work.

368
00:18:53,214 --> 00:18:54,924
- Okay.
- You think you can do that?

369
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:58,637
You two look great together.

370
00:18:58,720 --> 00:18:59,846
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

371
00:19:00,347 --> 00:19:02,432
We don't have to worry
about being caught anymore.

372
00:19:02,766 --> 00:19:06,311
We'll do all the tough things together
and work hard.

373
00:19:06,394 --> 00:19:07,395
Okay.

374
00:19:07,687 --> 00:19:09,564
- Should we get matching rings?
- Should we?

375
00:19:09,648 --> 00:19:11,983
Matching rings?
You're getting rings already?

376
00:19:12,108 --> 00:19:14,110
If we want, why not?

377
00:19:14,194 --> 00:19:17,197
But it's too soon.
You just started dating.

378
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:18,782
Kids these days move fast.

379
00:19:19,616 --> 00:19:22,327
Wow, am I working
or watching a dating show?

380
00:19:23,244 --> 00:19:26,206
Poor Choi Bo-yoon,
she's so bitter and lonely.

381
00:19:26,456 --> 00:19:29,125
You're not the one to talk, okay?

382
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:30,710
You're just as single as I am.

383
00:19:30,794 --> 00:19:32,003
Hey, I...

384
00:19:32,462 --> 00:19:34,381
You know what? You know nothing.

385
00:19:34,464 --> 00:19:37,092
I have my Sua, at least.

386
00:19:37,926 --> 00:19:39,552
Hello, my baby!

387
00:19:39,636 --> 00:19:40,887
- Dad.
- Yeah?

388
00:19:40,970 --> 00:19:43,515
We're having an early dismissal
because of a blackout.

389
00:19:43,598 --> 00:19:44,891
Should I pick you up, then?

390
00:19:44,974 --> 00:19:46,768
No, come after work.

391
00:19:46,851 --> 00:19:48,269
I'm hanging out with Min-gyu.

392
00:19:48,645 --> 00:19:50,146
Min-gyu? Who's that?

393
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:52,691
My boyfriend. Did I not tell you?

394
00:19:53,191 --> 00:19:54,359
Your boyfriend?

395
00:19:57,362 --> 00:20:01,282
I told her to ask me for permission,
whether it's a guy friend or a boyfriend!

396
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:04,202
Why is she already dating someone?
She's in kindergarten!

397
00:20:05,954 --> 00:20:08,790
Tae-seop's left me, and now, Jin-su.

398
00:20:08,957 --> 00:20:09,958
Sua!

399
00:20:12,001 --> 00:20:13,962
Oh, you must be Min-gyu.

400
00:20:14,045 --> 00:20:15,296
Hello.

401
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:18,383
Good to know my Sua has good taste.

402
00:20:18,466 --> 00:20:19,551
Are you two alone?

403
00:20:21,136 --> 00:20:22,387
Mom!

404
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,286
Alright!

405
00:20:46,369 --> 00:20:47,620
- Mom.
- Yeah?

406
00:20:47,704 --> 00:20:49,456
Sua's dad gave me soap bubbles.

407
00:20:49,539 --> 00:20:51,750
Really? Did you thank him?

408
00:20:52,083 --> 00:20:53,293
Go and thank him.

409
00:20:53,918 --> 00:20:55,670
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

410
00:20:56,212 --> 00:20:59,132
- Go and play with Sua.
- He was raised by good parents.

411
00:20:59,215 --> 00:21:00,258
Thank you.

412
00:21:00,341 --> 00:21:01,426
It's nothing.

413
00:21:02,469 --> 00:21:06,222
It's my first time hearing about Min-gyu.

414
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:09,517
That's because we only recently moved here

415
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:11,936
after my divorce from his dad.

416
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:13,104
I see.

417
00:21:14,272 --> 00:21:15,857
Well, my wife's passed away.

418
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:18,276
I see.

419
00:21:20,278 --> 00:21:24,783
I was worried about Min-gyu settling in
because he's so shy

420
00:21:25,992 --> 00:21:29,370
but I'm so glad
he got so close to Sua so quickly.

421
00:21:29,454 --> 00:21:32,624
Sua gets along with everyone.

422
00:21:32,832 --> 00:21:34,584
Let's be friends, too.

423
00:21:36,711 --> 00:21:38,004
Sure.

424
00:21:40,006 --> 00:21:41,841
Looks like they'll be here for a while.

425
00:21:41,925 --> 00:21:44,052
Do you want to have dinner nearby?

426
00:21:45,011 --> 00:21:46,721
I'm sure you don't want to cook at home.

427
00:21:49,224 --> 00:21:51,768
Oh, yeah, that's true, but...

428
00:21:52,435 --> 00:21:53,478
What about kalguksu?

429
00:21:55,104 --> 00:21:58,274
Do you like it?

430
00:22:00,026 --> 00:22:01,027
Yeah.

431
00:22:02,529 --> 00:22:04,030
I think I'll like it.

432
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:30,473
- Hello.
- Hey.

433
00:22:31,391 --> 00:22:33,017
Is something going on upstairs?

434
00:22:33,226 --> 00:22:36,229
Ji-su's doing a magazine interview here.

435
00:22:37,272 --> 00:22:39,274
- That's great.
- But you can get coffee.

436
00:22:39,357 --> 00:22:41,901
We'll take two lattes for takeout.

437
00:22:41,985 --> 00:22:43,069
Okay.

438
00:22:43,361 --> 00:22:46,281
Should we go upstairs and watch for a bit
before we go?

439
00:22:47,323 --> 00:22:48,449
Can we do that?

440
00:22:48,533 --> 00:22:49,534
Of course.

441
00:22:50,159 --> 00:22:51,411
Should we do that, then?

442
00:22:51,619 --> 00:22:53,788
Could you say something
about Ms. Son Jeong-a

443
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:57,041
who must be very special to you?

444
00:22:58,918 --> 00:23:02,297
Jeong-a was so charismatic on the set.

445
00:23:03,256 --> 00:23:06,009
I could feel her focus while acting

446
00:23:06,342 --> 00:23:08,261
and passion on the set very well.

447
00:23:08,344 --> 00:23:09,929
- He looks legit!
- I learned a lot.

448
00:23:10,013 --> 00:23:11,639
- If I get another chance
- Yeah.

449
00:23:11,723 --> 00:23:13,850
I'd love to work with her again.

450
00:23:14,976 --> 00:23:16,019
I see.

451
00:23:16,477 --> 00:23:19,355
What kind of actor do you want to become?

452
00:23:35,663 --> 00:23:37,248
Whatever it is

453
00:23:40,084 --> 00:23:42,253
don't try so hard to run from it.

454
00:23:43,463 --> 00:23:45,673
Use that time and effort

455
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:49,510
to stand for what you love.

456
00:23:52,972 --> 00:23:54,807
I'm sure there are things you love.

457
00:23:57,810 --> 00:24:00,855
Do that for a day, a month, then a year.

458
00:24:02,106 --> 00:24:03,775
Keep it up

459
00:24:05,485 --> 00:24:09,072
and one day, you'll feel just fine.

460
00:24:18,289 --> 00:24:20,041
My friend once told me

461
00:24:22,293 --> 00:24:26,214
to stand for what I love.

462
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:33,388
So, I looked deep inside myself

463
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:39,936
and realized I loved acting.

464
00:24:42,105 --> 00:24:45,608
She really challenged
the way I used to think.

465
00:24:47,193 --> 00:24:49,529
Instead of setting a certain direction
for myself

466
00:24:50,113 --> 00:24:53,408
I want to focus on the present
and chase what makes my heart beat.

467
00:24:54,993 --> 00:24:56,911
- That's incredible.
- Should we get going?

468
00:24:57,328 --> 00:24:58,538
Yeah, let's go.

469
00:25:09,215 --> 00:25:11,884
So, I want to work
on a romance project next.

470
00:25:12,468 --> 00:25:14,595
I want it to be a happy, loving story.

471
00:25:16,222 --> 00:25:17,682
I want to find love in a role

472
00:25:17,765 --> 00:25:20,518
and live the life I couldn't live
in reality.

473
00:25:20,643 --> 00:25:22,687
- I hope you get that role.
- Thanks.

474
00:25:31,237 --> 00:25:32,947
Ji-su's so amazing.

475
00:25:33,573 --> 00:25:34,907
He is.

476
00:25:36,951 --> 00:25:37,952
Alright.

477
00:25:43,624 --> 00:25:45,334
If everyone's free this weekend

478
00:25:45,418 --> 00:25:47,754
why don't we have an Eat Eat Club meeting
this weekend?

479
00:25:47,837 --> 00:25:49,130
I have something to say.

480
00:25:49,630 --> 00:25:50,715
Sounds good!

481
00:25:51,466 --> 00:25:52,717
Sounds good!

482
00:25:58,097 --> 00:25:59,557
I have something to tell you.

483
00:26:00,058 --> 00:26:01,100
What is it?

484
00:26:01,184 --> 00:26:03,436
I'm moving in with Jun.

485
00:26:03,519 --> 00:26:05,855
Huh? You two are...

486
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:07,899
moving in together?

487
00:26:09,650 --> 00:26:11,903
He was tight on money
with the gym rent being raised

488
00:26:11,986 --> 00:26:15,323
so I told him to move in with me
with just his toothbrush.

489
00:26:15,448 --> 00:26:17,617
It took him a few days to think about it

490
00:26:17,909 --> 00:26:19,202
but he eventually said yes.

491
00:26:19,744 --> 00:26:22,747
Hold up. Isn't it too soon?

492
00:26:23,331 --> 00:26:24,832
Wouldn't you feel uncomfortable?

493
00:26:25,041 --> 00:26:28,961
It's fine. He comes home late
and just sleeps all day.

494
00:26:29,045 --> 00:26:31,589
And we were always compatible...

495
00:26:34,383 --> 00:26:35,802
in bed, anyway.

496
00:26:38,221 --> 00:26:39,764
Are you really sure?

497
00:26:41,057 --> 00:26:45,019
I didn't give it a lot of thought
before going ahead with it.

498
00:26:45,103 --> 00:26:46,979
I just felt bad for him.

499
00:26:47,313 --> 00:26:49,357
It's not because he's my boyfriend.

500
00:26:49,732 --> 00:26:53,653
I've just never seen anyone
so earnest and hardworking.

501
00:26:54,612 --> 00:26:55,947
I see your point.

502
00:26:56,030 --> 00:26:58,116
Life is so tough

503
00:26:58,366 --> 00:27:01,953
so I want to be my Jun's lucky charm.

504
00:27:04,705 --> 00:27:06,457
You've changed.

505
00:27:07,291 --> 00:27:09,001
You've gotten more serious.

506
00:27:10,545 --> 00:27:12,255
Or should I say you grew up?

507
00:27:13,047 --> 00:27:14,423
- Really?
- Yeah.

508
00:27:16,843 --> 00:27:18,845
I already have a mature body!

509
00:27:18,928 --> 00:27:21,430
It's too dangerous
if I actually become mature, too.

510
00:27:22,056 --> 00:27:23,766
- Aren't I right?
- My gosh.

511
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:25,852
I take back what I just said.

512
00:27:25,935 --> 00:27:26,978
Forget I ever said that.

513
00:27:29,689 --> 00:27:32,692
I should ask if I can invite Jun
to the Eat Eat Club, too.

514
00:27:33,151 --> 00:27:34,694
- You're okay with it, right?
- Yeah.

515
00:27:34,861 --> 00:27:35,862
Sounds fine with me.

516
00:27:35,945 --> 00:27:38,364
He's family now.
I have to make sure he eats well.

517
00:27:38,447 --> 00:27:41,409
- Already?
- Ui-yeong!

518
00:27:41,742 --> 00:27:43,452
Can we have a word? And Hyun-min, too.

519
00:27:43,536 --> 00:27:45,788
- Okay.
- Okay.

520
00:27:49,208 --> 00:27:51,586
- About the fruit shipment yesterday.
- Yes?

521
00:27:51,669 --> 00:27:53,754
The quality is too inconsistent.

522
00:27:54,172 --> 00:27:57,466
The Restaurant Department just complained,
saying they couldn't cook with them.

523
00:27:57,758 --> 00:27:59,760
Every box tastes different.

524
00:27:59,844 --> 00:28:02,263
Have you not been managing our suppliers
while I was gone?

525
00:28:02,346 --> 00:28:05,057
We checked them when we received them.

526
00:28:05,141 --> 00:28:07,977
You should've done a better job, then.

527
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:11,105
Are you going to do a half-assed job
with everything now?

528
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:14,901
Didn't we get yesterday's shipment
from K Fruits?

529
00:28:16,110 --> 00:28:18,404
You were the one who signed with them...

530
00:28:19,488 --> 00:28:20,823
Stop it.

531
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:25,036
Can you just make sure
we don't have more issues?

532
00:28:25,995 --> 00:28:27,663
Where's Na-ri?

533
00:28:33,961 --> 00:28:35,546
I had to check some docs.

534
00:28:35,630 --> 00:28:37,131
Regarding the fruit complaint.

535
00:28:37,215 --> 00:28:40,760
Yeah, I was just warning them right now.

536
00:28:41,260 --> 00:28:42,303
You were the one

537
00:28:42,595 --> 00:28:44,680
who recommended that supplier.

538
00:28:44,764 --> 00:28:46,682
You did the site visit by yourself, too.

539
00:28:46,766 --> 00:28:49,060
You're the one who messed up
with this supplier

540
00:28:49,143 --> 00:28:51,562
so why are you scolding
our innocent employees?

541
00:28:52,772 --> 00:28:53,981
What did you say?

542
00:28:54,899 --> 00:28:57,318
What do you mean that I signed them?

543
00:28:58,027 --> 00:28:59,362
Oh, yeah, I visited them.

544
00:28:59,946 --> 00:29:02,990
Ui-yeong, it was a part of the contract
to check the quality

545
00:29:03,074 --> 00:29:06,827
so return the whole shipment to K Fruits
and make another order.

546
00:29:07,161 --> 00:29:12,041
Oh, and tell them we'll cut ties with them
if they mess up like this again.

547
00:29:12,667 --> 00:29:14,126
Okay, got it.

548
00:29:15,670 --> 00:29:17,046
Okay, that's sorted.

549
00:29:17,129 --> 00:29:20,466
But I heard you agreed to Marketing
moving up the new menu release

550
00:29:20,549 --> 00:29:22,843
without consulting us.

551
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:25,429
- We were...
- Shouldn't you have discussed it

552
00:29:25,513 --> 00:29:28,432
with your team first
before going forward with it?

553
00:29:28,891 --> 00:29:32,061
We don't appreciate the way you do things.

554
00:29:32,144 --> 00:29:35,856
We worked tirelessly to cover for you
while you were gone.

555
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:38,359
But we realized

556
00:29:38,734 --> 00:29:40,528
your absence didn't affect us much.

557
00:29:41,404 --> 00:29:43,406
With Ui-yeong, in particular.

558
00:29:54,333 --> 00:29:57,295
Are you here as my interior designer
or as a customer?

559
00:29:59,005 --> 00:30:01,132
About these rings...

560
00:30:01,549 --> 00:30:03,676
Could you make them one more time?

561
00:30:05,261 --> 00:30:07,471
- For you and your girlfriend?
- Yeah.

562
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:15,062
Sure, I can make a special exception
just for you.

563
00:30:17,023 --> 00:30:19,066
Do you know your girlfriend's ring size?

564
00:30:20,067 --> 00:30:22,403
I'm not really sure. What do I do?

565
00:30:22,486 --> 00:30:25,364
You can ask for her ring size
or bring a ring she wears.

566
00:30:25,448 --> 00:30:27,700
Oh, yeah, she wears a lot of rings.

567
00:30:28,242 --> 00:30:29,744
Should I steal one from her?

568
00:30:31,245 --> 00:30:34,206
I can't work on the rings for a while
once you start the renovation

569
00:30:34,457 --> 00:30:35,499
so hurry.

570
00:30:35,583 --> 00:30:37,001
Okay, thank you.

571
00:30:45,551 --> 00:30:46,802
So, that's how it's done.

572
00:30:49,555 --> 00:30:50,681
I love that guy.

573
00:30:53,851 --> 00:30:54,894
I'm hungry.

574
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,814
That's so cool.

575
00:31:08,991 --> 00:31:10,659
Let's go there one day, okay?

576
00:31:11,911 --> 00:31:12,912
Let's go there.

577
00:31:13,496 --> 00:31:15,956
Yeah, I wanted to go, too.

578
00:31:20,669 --> 00:31:21,796
So, that's how they do it.

579
00:31:21,879 --> 00:31:23,214
- Just a sec.
- Okay.

580
00:31:26,592 --> 00:31:28,135
Oh, hi, Mr. Eun.

581
00:31:28,594 --> 00:31:30,304
- Hey, Ui-yeong.
- Hi.

582
00:31:30,388 --> 00:31:32,348
Sorry for calling you so late.

583
00:31:32,431 --> 00:31:33,432
It's okay.

584
00:31:33,516 --> 00:31:36,811
You know your friend
who's getting married next week?

585
00:31:36,894 --> 00:31:39,021
- Yeah, Eun-mi?
- Yes.

586
00:31:39,105 --> 00:31:42,274
The manager in charge of the event
just got a call

587
00:31:42,358 --> 00:31:45,736
asking how much it'd cost
to cancel the wedding now.

588
00:31:45,820 --> 00:31:48,322
Did she? And did she cancel it?

589
00:31:48,406 --> 00:31:49,532
No.

590
00:31:49,657 --> 00:31:52,785
She was surprised by how much it'd cost
and hung up.

591
00:31:53,244 --> 00:31:56,705
But she didn't sound like she was okay

592
00:31:56,914 --> 00:31:58,999
so I thought I should tell you.

593
00:31:59,834 --> 00:32:02,586
Okay, thank you.

594
00:32:04,588 --> 00:32:06,632
What's wrong?
Something wrong with your finger...

595
00:32:07,341 --> 00:32:09,009
No, something wrong with your friend?

596
00:32:09,552 --> 00:32:12,721
She asked if she could cancel the wedding.

597
00:32:12,805 --> 00:32:13,806
Hmm?

598
00:32:14,140 --> 00:32:16,475
- I'd better call her.
- Yeah.

599
00:32:18,519 --> 00:32:19,562
What's going on?

600
00:32:30,030 --> 00:32:31,282
- Hello.
- Hello.

601
00:32:31,365 --> 00:32:33,451
- Who's the reservation for?
- Lee Eun-mi.

602
00:32:33,534 --> 00:32:35,035
- Oh, come this way.
- Okay.

603
00:32:42,251 --> 00:32:43,919
It's the dress for your wedding, right?

604
00:32:44,753 --> 00:32:46,213
You chose a great one!

605
00:32:46,297 --> 00:32:47,673
It suits you so well.

606
00:32:47,756 --> 00:32:49,592
I'll get it ready
so that you can try it on.

607
00:32:49,758 --> 00:32:53,053
Oh, I'm not the bride. It's my friend.

608
00:32:53,929 --> 00:32:55,890
- Oh, sorry!
- It's okay.

609
00:32:55,973 --> 00:32:58,476
Brides usually come alone
on the last fitting day.

610
00:32:59,101 --> 00:33:00,811
Please sit and wait here.

611
00:33:00,895 --> 00:33:02,021
Okay, thank you.

612
00:33:11,780 --> 00:33:15,326
I just wanted to check
how much the cancellation would be.

613
00:33:17,536 --> 00:33:20,080
You sure nothing's wrong?

614
00:33:20,164 --> 00:33:21,916
No, everything's fine.

615
00:33:22,458 --> 00:33:25,127
I just thought
I was supposed to get married by now.

616
00:33:25,586 --> 00:33:29,256
And I know it's not easy to find a guy
who checks all the boxes like my fiancé.

617
00:33:30,466 --> 00:33:32,801
But I don't know why I'm so nervous.

618
00:33:33,302 --> 00:33:37,264
I'm really not sure if this is the man
I should commit the rest of my life to.

619
00:33:40,726 --> 00:33:45,356
You must be feeling overwhelmed
with the wedding coming up so soon

620
00:33:45,940 --> 00:33:50,027
but I hear it's common to get
that "marriage blues."

621
00:33:56,700 --> 00:33:59,787
Eun-mi, you look stunning.

622
00:34:07,336 --> 00:34:09,880
Yeah, I lost so much weight for this.

623
00:34:10,047 --> 00:34:11,382
And spent so much money.

624
00:34:12,216 --> 00:34:14,385
I can't cancel the wedding
after inviting everyone.

625
00:34:14,927 --> 00:34:16,762
I'd even embarrass my parents.

626
00:34:18,472 --> 00:34:19,640
I have to go ahead with it.

627
00:34:23,018 --> 00:34:24,061
It looks great.

628
00:34:24,228 --> 00:34:25,354
Yeah, it's beautiful.

629
00:34:31,443 --> 00:34:33,487
Do you really have to get divorced?

630
00:34:33,654 --> 00:34:35,447
Are you sure you won't change your mind?

631
00:34:35,823 --> 00:34:37,199
Yeah, I'm sure of it.

632
00:34:37,533 --> 00:34:40,452
We don't have a lot of time left to live.
Let's enjoy it in peace.

633
00:34:41,287 --> 00:34:42,288
Fine.

634
00:34:42,955 --> 00:34:44,415
See you at the court next week.

635
00:34:55,759 --> 00:34:57,052
ORGANIC FERTILIZER

636
00:34:57,136 --> 00:34:59,346
- I'm home!
- Hey.

637
00:34:59,430 --> 00:35:01,974
What are you doing? Repotting the plants?

638
00:35:02,057 --> 00:35:04,393
Yeah, I've been putting it off
for a while.

639
00:35:05,311 --> 00:35:08,689
I thought this was fully grown
because it stopped growing.

640
00:35:08,772 --> 00:35:09,773
Oh.

641
00:35:10,232 --> 00:35:13,694
It stopped growing because the roots had
no more space to expand into.

642
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:17,406
It realized that this was
as tall as it could become in this pot.

643
00:35:18,699 --> 00:35:21,994
- Do you want me to help?
- No, you'll get dirt on your clothes.

644
00:35:22,494 --> 00:35:24,496
Right. Your dad texted me.

645
00:35:25,456 --> 00:35:27,791
Yeah? What did he say?

646
00:35:28,167 --> 00:35:29,793
He agreed to getting divorced.

647
00:35:32,171 --> 00:35:34,340
We're meeting at court next week.

648
00:35:37,259 --> 00:35:39,803
Okay, I'll keep that in mind.

649
00:35:40,095 --> 00:35:41,096
Okay.

650
00:36:00,407 --> 00:36:03,243
SPEECH FOR THE WEDDING TOAST

651
00:36:06,413 --> 00:36:08,415
In the fairy tales I read as a kid,

652
00:36:08,499 --> 00:36:10,459
marriage was
the definition of a happy ending.

653
00:36:11,877 --> 00:36:14,171
But now that I'm older

654
00:36:14,880 --> 00:36:16,965
I completely understand my friend's fear

655
00:36:17,049 --> 00:36:19,510
at the thought of spending her life
with one man.

656
00:36:20,636 --> 00:36:21,804
And my mom's divorce looks

657
00:36:22,346 --> 00:36:25,307
like a happy ending
where she gets her life back.

658
00:36:27,017 --> 00:36:31,438
So, why do people choose to get married?

659
00:36:37,778 --> 00:36:38,946
Hello

660
00:36:39,029 --> 00:36:42,491
I'm Lee Ui-yeong,
a friend of the bride, Eun-mi.

661
00:36:43,242 --> 00:36:46,870
It's a huge honor to join
the lovely couple today

662
00:36:48,330 --> 00:36:49,790
in their most precious moment.

663
00:36:50,833 --> 00:36:53,293
For the two to get here...

664
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:59,675
What brings you here out of the blue?
You should've come in.

665
00:37:00,175 --> 00:37:02,678
Aren't you joining us
for the Eat Eat Club meeting today?

666
00:37:02,928 --> 00:37:05,723
I wanted to ask you something before that.

667
00:37:06,390 --> 00:37:07,391
Huh?

668
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:14,940
So, you want to surprise her with a ring

669
00:37:15,274 --> 00:37:17,151
- but don't know her size?
- No.

670
00:37:17,776 --> 00:37:20,738
I tried to measure her finger
without her knowing, but it wasn't easy.

671
00:37:21,155 --> 00:37:24,783
Could you casually ask her for me
without her noticing anything?

672
00:37:27,828 --> 00:37:31,248
Are you trying to do
what the young ones do these days

673
00:37:31,331 --> 00:37:33,333
and propose to her?

674
00:37:33,417 --> 00:37:35,127
No, it's not like that.

675
00:37:35,210 --> 00:37:38,172
Why not? Isn't it about time
you think about getting married?

676
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:41,717
I'm always open to it

677
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:43,635
but it's not something I can do alone.

678
00:37:44,428 --> 00:37:48,307
I'm just waiting for Ui-yeong
to become interested in it.

679
00:37:48,390 --> 00:37:49,641
Don't worry, I got you.

680
00:37:49,725 --> 00:37:52,853
I'm the Cupid for you two. Just trust me.

681
00:37:52,978 --> 00:37:55,856
I'll get those rings
on both of your fingers.

682
00:37:56,482 --> 00:37:57,483
Okay.

683
00:38:07,409 --> 00:38:09,244
- Eat up.
- Could I have some soup?

684
00:38:09,328 --> 00:38:11,121
This is milt. It's a specialty.

685
00:38:11,830 --> 00:38:13,791
I'll mix the drinks my way.

686
00:38:13,874 --> 00:38:15,959
Oh, yeah, drinks! Tae-seop!

687
00:38:16,168 --> 00:38:17,169
Oh, right.

688
00:38:17,252 --> 00:38:19,630
My mom's taking care
of the drinks tonight.

689
00:38:19,713 --> 00:38:21,089
Drink whatever you want.

690
00:38:21,173 --> 00:38:22,341
The owner said it was okay.

691
00:38:22,883 --> 00:38:24,468
- Those are some good ones.
- Yeah.

692
00:38:24,551 --> 00:38:26,762
- Should we start with the expensive one?
- Right on!

693
00:38:26,845 --> 00:38:28,722
- I'll pour them into soju glasses.
- Okay.

694
00:38:28,806 --> 00:38:31,016
- Please thank your mom for us.
- Okay.

695
00:38:31,099 --> 00:38:34,061
My mom's trying to get healthy.

696
00:38:34,228 --> 00:38:35,604
With that said, Seung-jun

697
00:38:35,687 --> 00:38:38,065
sign my mom and me up
for ten personal trainer sessions.

698
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:39,441
- Really?
- Yeah.

699
00:38:39,525 --> 00:38:40,692
I'll take 20 classes, then.

700
00:38:41,151 --> 00:38:43,070
- It'll be fun to work out together.
- Yeah!

701
00:38:44,655 --> 00:38:45,823
- Thank you.
- It's nothing.

702
00:38:45,906 --> 00:38:48,242
I'll give all of you
three extra sessions, then.

703
00:38:48,325 --> 00:38:49,827
Right on!

704
00:38:50,702 --> 00:38:52,621
Is Sae-byeok not coming?

705
00:38:52,704 --> 00:38:55,707
She had tickets to a show,
and couldn't cancel it.

706
00:38:55,791 --> 00:38:58,669
I guess she's busy dating her colleague!

707
00:38:58,752 --> 00:39:00,045
- So cute.
- Really?

708
00:39:00,170 --> 00:39:02,464
I wanted to break the news
with everyone around.

709
00:39:03,966 --> 00:39:07,845
I'm quitting at the hotel soon
and leaving the country.

710
00:39:08,387 --> 00:39:10,430
That's so sudden.

711
00:39:10,556 --> 00:39:11,932
Where are you going?

712
00:39:12,015 --> 00:39:15,227
I've been offered the Head Chef position
at a fusion restaurant in New York.

713
00:39:16,812 --> 00:39:19,398
I thought I'd announce it
before we started eating.

714
00:39:20,566 --> 00:39:21,984
Congratulations!

715
00:39:22,067 --> 00:39:23,068
Congratulations.

716
00:39:23,151 --> 00:39:24,695
- Thank you.
- Congratulations!

717
00:39:24,778 --> 00:39:26,572
But could you stay with us a bit longer?

718
00:39:27,364 --> 00:39:28,740
- Mr. Eun!
- Yeah?

719
00:39:28,824 --> 00:39:31,201
How can you let
such a talented chef leave?

720
00:39:31,285 --> 00:39:34,079
If that's what she wants, what can I do?

721
00:39:34,162 --> 00:39:37,040
Chefs never stay at a place
for all that long.

722
00:39:37,124 --> 00:39:39,626
We always move to another place
where we can improve.

723
00:39:40,586 --> 00:39:43,505
But thanks to you,
I got to try chicken feet

724
00:39:44,631 --> 00:39:46,717
gaebul, sundae

725
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,302
and now, fresh daegu-tang.

726
00:39:48,594 --> 00:39:50,053
This was a huge inspiration.

727
00:39:50,846 --> 00:39:54,224
I'm glad the Eat Eat Club took a part
in your growth.

728
00:39:54,892 --> 00:39:56,560
Alright, let's dig in.

729
00:39:57,019 --> 00:39:59,688
- Cheers! Congrats!
- Congrats!

730
00:39:59,771 --> 00:40:01,315
- Congrats!
- It's on me today.

731
00:40:01,398 --> 00:40:02,733
- Really?
- My gosh!

732
00:40:02,816 --> 00:40:04,902
- Thank you.
- Thank you!

733
00:40:05,986 --> 00:40:09,990
I can't believe
Westerners only deep-fry cod.

734
00:40:12,701 --> 00:40:14,202
The broth is perfect!

735
00:40:14,286 --> 00:40:16,997
You can't forget about us
once you taste it.

736
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:19,333
Not at all. I can't forget this.

737
00:40:19,416 --> 00:40:20,500
It's good, right?

738
00:40:25,047 --> 00:40:28,467
Since we're all here,
I also have a question for everyone.

739
00:40:28,550 --> 00:40:29,718
What is it?

740
00:40:30,427 --> 00:40:35,849
I want to get a ring for my wife.

741
00:40:37,392 --> 00:40:39,478
What's your ring size, Ui-yeong?

742
00:40:39,561 --> 00:40:40,562
Me?

743
00:40:42,314 --> 00:40:46,777
Why are you asking Ui-yeong
when it's for your wife?

744
00:40:48,654 --> 00:40:49,655
Hmm?

745
00:40:51,740 --> 00:40:54,242
Her hands are as big as Ui-yeong's.

746
00:40:54,326 --> 00:40:55,619
Oh, really?

747
00:40:56,078 --> 00:40:57,996
- My size is...
- Yeah?

748
00:41:01,708 --> 00:41:02,751
I have no idea.

749
00:41:03,168 --> 00:41:05,087
I don't think anyone knows their size.
Do you?

750
00:41:05,212 --> 00:41:06,213
A small?

751
00:41:06,672 --> 00:41:07,881
I guess I'd be an x-small.

752
00:41:08,840 --> 00:41:10,217
I don't know it, either.

753
00:41:10,467 --> 00:41:11,510
I see.

754
00:41:11,927 --> 00:41:13,303
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

755
00:41:13,387 --> 00:41:14,972
Gosh, what should I do now?

756
00:41:16,098 --> 00:41:19,893
I thought you'd know
your wife's ring size.

757
00:41:19,977 --> 00:41:21,687
Since you're always so good to her.

758
00:41:21,895 --> 00:41:23,855
Honey, remember mine from now on.

759
00:41:23,939 --> 00:41:25,107
Check my left ring finger.

760
00:41:26,108 --> 00:41:27,943
- Thank you.
- Take the ring.

761
00:41:28,402 --> 00:41:29,486
Thank you.

762
00:41:30,195 --> 00:41:33,824
Gosh, I'm a huge disappointment today.

763
00:41:35,575 --> 00:41:36,785
My gosh.

764
00:41:37,953 --> 00:41:40,122
I don't know why I want soju

765
00:41:41,373 --> 00:41:42,958
with all these expensive drinks here.

766
00:41:43,750 --> 00:41:44,751
Man!

767
00:41:46,253 --> 00:41:48,088
Should I pour you a glass?

768
00:41:48,171 --> 00:41:49,172
Sure.

769
00:41:50,632 --> 00:41:52,092
- Oh, my!
- Slow down.

770
00:42:07,149 --> 00:42:08,150
Ui-yeong

771
00:42:08,775 --> 00:42:12,529
I'm going back home
after filing my divorce at the court

772
00:42:12,821 --> 00:42:13,905
with your mom.

773
00:42:15,365 --> 00:42:17,659
Sorry for causing you so much trouble.

774
00:42:18,493 --> 00:42:20,829
Let's meet up once things are sorted.

775
00:42:28,128 --> 00:42:30,797
SONGI SPICY CHICKEN FEET

776
00:42:42,559 --> 00:42:44,186
Rice balls? Okay!

777
00:42:46,021 --> 00:42:47,064
Hello!

778
00:42:47,147 --> 00:42:48,398
Can I get takeout?

779
00:42:48,482 --> 00:42:49,691
Of course!

780
00:42:49,775 --> 00:42:51,234
How many people is it for?

781
00:42:51,318 --> 00:42:52,319
- Two.
- Two?

782
00:42:52,402 --> 00:42:54,237
I'll prepare a medium, then.

783
00:42:54,321 --> 00:42:55,572
I have a takeout order!

784
00:42:55,655 --> 00:42:57,741
Feel free to wait upstairs.

785
00:42:57,824 --> 00:42:59,409
- I'll bring it right to you.
- Okay.

786
00:42:59,618 --> 00:43:01,453
Honey, a medium for takeout!

787
00:43:01,536 --> 00:43:02,829
SEOUL FAMILY COURT

788
00:43:06,249 --> 00:43:08,376
Here are your rice balls.

789
00:43:09,294 --> 00:43:11,421
BELOVED TREASURE
WE'RE ALL A TREASURE TO SOMEONE

790
00:43:16,301 --> 00:43:19,096
- My son hung that up for us.
- I see.

791
00:43:19,304 --> 00:43:22,099
You know how we forget
about how precious we are

792
00:43:22,182 --> 00:43:23,391
when life gets crazy.

793
00:43:23,475 --> 00:43:25,310
I wanted my customers to remember it

794
00:43:25,560 --> 00:43:27,646
at least when they were eating
their chicken feet.

795
00:43:28,063 --> 00:43:29,439
This is on the house.

796
00:43:29,523 --> 00:43:31,399
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

797
00:43:32,275 --> 00:43:35,153
But I feel like your son wrote it

798
00:43:35,570 --> 00:43:38,365
as a reminder to all your customers
that they should respect you

799
00:43:38,448 --> 00:43:40,492
because you're precious.

800
00:43:42,994 --> 00:43:44,079
You think so?

801
00:43:45,872 --> 00:43:50,794
Well, I guess my son is
the most thoughtful person ever.

802
00:43:51,920 --> 00:43:54,381
By the way,
it's your first time here, right?

803
00:43:54,464 --> 00:43:55,841
Yeah, it's my first time

804
00:43:55,924 --> 00:43:57,968
but my daughter loves
the chicken feet here.

805
00:43:58,051 --> 00:44:00,512
- Your daughter must be a regular!
- Yeah.

806
00:44:01,012 --> 00:44:04,349
She has good taste, you know?

807
00:44:04,432 --> 00:44:05,433
I see.

808
00:44:05,517 --> 00:44:07,561
She has a keen eye

809
00:44:07,644 --> 00:44:09,646
for good ingredients and flavors in food.

810
00:44:09,938 --> 00:44:11,231
Hold on.

811
00:44:11,690 --> 00:44:16,069
I know most of my regulars.

812
00:44:16,611 --> 00:44:18,321
Oh, now that I think about it

813
00:44:18,405 --> 00:44:23,493
the way your lips curve when you smile...

814
00:44:23,743 --> 00:44:26,121
Just kidding, I hvae no idea.

815
00:44:28,582 --> 00:44:30,125
I'll come with her next time.

816
00:44:30,208 --> 00:44:33,545
Sure, come with her

817
00:44:33,628 --> 00:44:37,007
and I'll give you
steamed eggs and rice on the house.

818
00:44:37,090 --> 00:44:39,050
- Okay, thank you.
- I'll bring your food soon.

819
00:44:39,134 --> 00:44:40,302
Thank you.

820
00:44:43,013 --> 00:44:44,014
I can't wait to try it.

821
00:44:46,224 --> 00:44:48,935
Oh, your parents went to court today.

822
00:44:49,477 --> 00:44:50,687
Yeah.

823
00:44:51,563 --> 00:44:53,064
I thought about going with Mom

824
00:44:53,481 --> 00:44:56,234
but it seemed
like they wanted to end things peacefully.

825
00:44:56,943 --> 00:44:57,986
Good choice.

826
00:44:58,069 --> 00:44:59,863
Tae-seop, you know the chair?

827
00:45:00,238 --> 00:45:02,365
- I'm sitting in it right now.
- Okay.

828
00:45:02,449 --> 00:45:03,950
What's wrong? Is it uncomfortable?

829
00:45:04,284 --> 00:45:06,494
No, it's the opposite.

830
00:45:06,953 --> 00:45:10,373
See how I'm talking
about my parents' divorce so peacefully?

831
00:45:11,875 --> 00:45:12,918
Well

832
00:45:13,543 --> 00:45:15,295
there's a secret to it.

833
00:45:15,378 --> 00:45:16,463
What is it?

834
00:45:16,546 --> 00:45:20,300
The back panel leans back
at seven degrees.

835
00:45:20,759 --> 00:45:22,802
That tiny change makes it
so comfortable, right?

836
00:45:23,595 --> 00:45:25,055
Yeah, it's the best.

837
00:45:25,764 --> 00:45:29,100
I always have your back, too

838
00:45:29,601 --> 00:45:30,936
so lean on me anytime.

839
00:45:31,686 --> 00:45:32,729
Okay.

840
00:45:33,521 --> 00:45:34,898
Oh, my mom's home.

841
00:45:34,981 --> 00:45:36,566
- I'll call you later.
- Okay.

842
00:45:37,275 --> 00:45:39,277
- Hey, Mom.
- Hey.

843
00:45:40,111 --> 00:45:41,112
What's that?

844
00:45:41,279 --> 00:45:42,864
- You haven't had dinner, right?
- No.

845
00:45:43,156 --> 00:45:44,449
- I got your favorite.
- What?

846
00:45:44,532 --> 00:45:45,575
SONGI SPICY CHICKEN FEET

847
00:45:46,451 --> 00:45:48,119
- Songi Spicy Chicken Feet?
- Yeah.

848
00:45:53,458 --> 00:45:56,878
So, the owner that I met today is
Tae-seop's mom?

849
00:45:56,962 --> 00:46:00,257
Yeah! I was so surprised
when I first found out.

850
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:01,341
Small world, huh?

851
00:46:03,093 --> 00:46:06,221
- Does kindness run in the family?
- What?

852
00:46:06,596 --> 00:46:09,724
She gave me a can of soda on the house
when I was waiting for the food.

853
00:46:10,225 --> 00:46:11,977
- Did she?
- Yeah.

854
00:46:20,485 --> 00:46:21,778
Mom

855
00:46:22,279 --> 00:46:24,406
did everything go smoothly at the court?

856
00:46:25,532 --> 00:46:26,533
Yeah.

857
00:46:27,659 --> 00:46:29,577
Nothing happened. It was quick.

858
00:46:30,495 --> 00:46:32,664
Oh, we have to be back in a month.

859
00:46:33,540 --> 00:46:36,668
I feel so liberated now.
I don't know why I took so long.

860
00:46:40,005 --> 00:46:41,715
- Mom
- Hmm?

861
00:46:42,299 --> 00:46:45,302
you wouldn't get married
if you could go back in time, right?

862
00:46:47,971 --> 00:46:49,264
I think I'd still do it.

863
00:46:49,347 --> 00:46:50,432
You would?

864
00:46:51,141 --> 00:46:54,144
Sure, we separated in the end

865
00:46:54,477 --> 00:46:58,440
but that was the best choice I could make
in that point in life.

866
00:46:58,648 --> 00:47:02,068
So, even if I were to go back,
I'd probably choose the same.

867
00:47:03,778 --> 00:47:06,239
What if you went back in time
with these memories?

868
00:47:06,656 --> 00:47:08,783
People think about this all the time.

869
00:47:09,284 --> 00:47:11,786
I'd try even harder to make
the exact same choices, then.

870
00:47:11,870 --> 00:47:13,455
So I can meet you again.

871
00:47:14,122 --> 00:47:16,958
What? Just to bring me into the world?

872
00:47:17,042 --> 00:47:19,169
Yeah, as wild as life gets

873
00:47:19,544 --> 00:47:21,379
being alive is fun.

874
00:47:22,213 --> 00:47:25,050
And I feel less lonely with you.

875
00:47:30,055 --> 00:47:32,307
Maybe I should take days off at work

876
00:47:32,724 --> 00:47:34,726
and enjoy my freedom on a trip.

877
00:47:35,310 --> 00:47:36,978
Maybe learn a new language, too.

878
00:47:37,062 --> 00:47:40,523
I've always wanted to learn Spanish.

879
00:47:41,358 --> 00:47:42,609
Should we go together?

880
00:47:42,692 --> 00:47:45,779
Should we get a savings account
to save for trips?

881
00:47:45,862 --> 00:47:47,405
- That's a great idea!
- Right?

882
00:47:47,864 --> 00:47:49,282
You can pay for 70% of it.

883
00:47:49,366 --> 00:47:52,202
I swear you're an evil stepmom.

884
00:48:12,013 --> 00:48:13,515
How do I look? Do I look okay?

885
00:48:13,598 --> 00:48:16,226
"Okay"? You look like an angel!

886
00:48:17,519 --> 00:48:20,021
I made sure to warm up my lips
for that speech.

887
00:48:20,355 --> 00:48:23,775
Make sure to stretch your facial muscles
because you're about to laugh nonstop.

888
00:48:26,528 --> 00:48:29,823
- Hey!
- Hey, you're here!

889
00:48:29,906 --> 00:48:32,242
- Come and take photos.
- Come and sit.

890
00:48:36,371 --> 00:48:38,164
- The main character.
- Ta-da!

891
00:48:38,915 --> 00:48:40,166
I feel so nervous.

892
00:48:43,837 --> 00:48:46,297
GUESTS FOR THE BRIDE

893
00:48:46,381 --> 00:48:48,258
I've heard a lot about you.

894
00:48:48,341 --> 00:48:49,884
Thank you.

895
00:48:49,968 --> 00:48:51,761
- Hello.
- Congratulations.

896
00:48:51,845 --> 00:48:53,471
- Thank you!
- He grew up so much!

897
00:48:53,555 --> 00:48:56,349
- My goodness!
- I haven't seen you in forever.

898
00:48:56,433 --> 00:48:59,144
- Don't they look so happy?
- The dress looks perfect on her!

899
00:48:59,227 --> 00:49:00,562
- She looks amazing.
- Right?

900
00:49:00,645 --> 00:49:02,897
- She looks like a princess.
- She looks so happy.

901
00:49:02,981 --> 00:49:04,107
- Right?
- Inspired yet?

902
00:49:04,190 --> 00:49:05,942
- Come on.
- Stop it.

903
00:49:07,193 --> 00:49:08,361
- I know.
- Ui-yeong.

904
00:49:08,445 --> 00:49:09,571
Oh, hi.

905
00:49:09,904 --> 00:49:10,947
That's my boyfriend.

906
00:49:11,614 --> 00:49:12,907
- Ui-yeong!
- No way!

907
00:49:12,991 --> 00:49:14,659
- He's so handsome!
- You think so?

908
00:49:14,742 --> 00:49:15,994
You met him on a blind date?

909
00:49:16,077 --> 00:49:17,912
How did you get a man like that?

910
00:49:17,996 --> 00:49:19,747
Say hi to my friends.

911
00:49:19,831 --> 00:49:21,249
Hello, I'm Song Tae-seop.

912
00:49:21,332 --> 00:49:22,459
- Hello.
- Hello.

913
00:49:22,542 --> 00:49:24,085
We're her friends from college.

914
00:49:24,169 --> 00:49:25,837
Yeah, she's told me a lot about you.

915
00:49:25,920 --> 00:49:27,338
Really?

916
00:49:27,547 --> 00:49:29,883
- You two look great together.
- Really?

917
00:49:29,966 --> 00:49:32,302
Let's go on double dates sometime.

918
00:49:32,385 --> 00:49:34,012
Sure, invite me anytime.

919
00:49:34,095 --> 00:49:35,138
Okay!

920
00:49:35,221 --> 00:49:36,890
- The wedding is about to begin.
- Let's go.

921
00:49:36,973 --> 00:49:38,683
- Should we head in?
- Yeah.

922
00:49:38,766 --> 00:49:39,851
- We'll go.
- See you!

923
00:49:39,934 --> 00:49:41,311
- See you.
- Bye.

924
00:49:41,978 --> 00:49:43,730
He's so handsome!

925
00:49:43,813 --> 00:49:45,356
Excuse me!

926
00:49:45,773 --> 00:49:47,358
You're a friend of the bride, right?

927
00:49:47,442 --> 00:49:50,862
Yes, is something wrong?

928
00:49:52,238 --> 00:49:53,531
The bride...

929
00:49:53,948 --> 00:49:55,283
won't come out.

930
00:49:55,825 --> 00:49:56,910
Sorry?

931
00:49:57,202 --> 00:49:58,828
She won't come out.

932
00:49:59,537 --> 00:50:00,538
Oh...

933
00:50:02,707 --> 00:50:03,917
This way.

934
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:06,753
BRIDE'S WAITING ROOM

935
00:50:06,961 --> 00:50:08,004
Here.

936
00:50:08,213 --> 00:50:10,590
She wanted to be left alone for a bit,
so I left her

937
00:50:10,673 --> 00:50:13,259
but now, she's locked the door
and won't even answer.

938
00:50:13,760 --> 00:50:15,929
Should I ask the venue manager
for the key?

939
00:50:17,222 --> 00:50:20,350
No, I'll try talking to her.

940
00:50:20,433 --> 00:50:21,434
Okay.

941
00:50:23,895 --> 00:50:25,897
I'll wait outside.

942
00:50:25,980 --> 00:50:27,023
Okay.

943
00:50:33,738 --> 00:50:36,074
Eun-mi, it's me.

944
00:50:39,077 --> 00:50:41,287
- Ui-yeong?
- Yeah.

945
00:50:41,621 --> 00:50:43,831
Are you okay? Are you not feeling well?

946
00:50:44,666 --> 00:50:47,418
My heart is beating too fast.
I feel like throwing up.

947
00:50:48,002 --> 00:50:49,879
And the dress is so suffocating.

948
00:50:50,964 --> 00:50:52,465
I did some research

949
00:50:52,632 --> 00:50:56,135
and it's still better to break up
and pay the penalty before the wedding.

950
00:50:56,594 --> 00:50:58,930
Eun-mi

951
00:50:59,013 --> 00:51:01,015
don't think about anything for now.

952
00:51:01,432 --> 00:51:03,685
Can you just open the door for me?

953
00:51:04,352 --> 00:51:05,603
I'm alone.

954
00:51:09,899 --> 00:51:10,984
Come on, Eun-mi.

955
00:51:15,363 --> 00:51:16,364
Eun-mi...

956
00:51:19,617 --> 00:51:20,785
It's okay.

957
00:51:21,995 --> 00:51:25,164
It's natural to feel nervous and scared.

958
00:51:27,083 --> 00:51:28,251
But...

959
00:51:29,294 --> 00:51:31,087
being scared of getting married

960
00:51:31,921 --> 00:51:35,967
and being unsure about the man himself
are different things.

961
00:51:38,386 --> 00:51:42,640
Did he really never feel
like he was the one?

962
00:51:51,983 --> 00:51:53,026
Ho-jin...

963
00:51:55,111 --> 00:51:56,362
Are you okay, Eun-mi?

964
00:51:56,738 --> 00:51:59,699
We really have to go now.

965
00:52:00,325 --> 00:52:01,367
It's okay.

966
00:52:01,784 --> 00:52:03,870
Being a little late isn't a big deal.

967
00:52:05,371 --> 00:52:06,414
Okay.

968
00:52:12,170 --> 00:52:13,296
I know it's been a lot.

969
00:52:21,095 --> 00:52:22,972
You've been in an uncomfortable dress
all day

970
00:52:23,681 --> 00:52:25,224
pretending to be completely fine.

971
00:52:26,434 --> 00:52:27,477
Eun-mi

972
00:52:27,894 --> 00:52:30,605
you don't have to go into the hall
if it's too much. It's fine.

973
00:52:33,107 --> 00:52:34,150
Ho-jin...

974
00:52:34,734 --> 00:52:35,818
It's okay.

975
00:52:37,445 --> 00:52:39,405
I'll always be by your side.

976
00:52:42,867 --> 00:52:43,910
Okay?

977
00:52:54,962 --> 00:52:56,631
I'm ready to go in.

978
00:52:59,217 --> 00:53:00,426
I'm ready.

979
00:53:05,056 --> 00:53:07,975
Hello, I'm the host of today's ceremony

980
00:53:08,059 --> 00:53:11,479
and the groom's friend, Yoo Jeong-hwa.

981
00:53:12,313 --> 00:53:15,566
On behalf of the bride and the groom

982
00:53:15,650 --> 00:53:18,403
as well as their families

983
00:53:18,486 --> 00:53:20,530
- What's wrong?
- thank you to everyone

984
00:53:20,613 --> 00:53:22,740
- for making time in your busy day.
- My speech is

985
00:53:22,824 --> 00:53:24,367
too oblivious.

986
00:53:24,784 --> 00:53:26,661
It's too happy.

987
00:53:28,371 --> 00:53:31,457
Just wing it, then.

988
00:53:31,541 --> 00:53:34,585
Whatever will be helpful,
as long as it's from your heart.

989
00:53:34,669 --> 00:53:37,547
Let's now begin
Jung Ho-jin and Lee Eun-mi's wedding.

990
00:53:38,047 --> 00:53:41,092
Please look to the back.

991
00:53:41,175 --> 00:53:45,930
The bride and the groom will now enter
in your blessing.

992
00:53:46,013 --> 00:53:48,891
Bride and groom, please enter.

993
00:53:51,602 --> 00:53:55,732
Please give them a big applause
to wish them a bright future.

994
00:53:58,317 --> 00:54:01,696
Friends, please cheer harder for them.

995
00:54:02,739 --> 00:54:05,700
The two are holding hands

996
00:54:05,783 --> 00:54:10,204
and calmly walking
toward a future together.

997
00:54:10,496 --> 00:54:13,082
You have taken your wedding vows

998
00:54:13,166 --> 00:54:16,961
to be with each other forevermore.

999
00:54:17,170 --> 00:54:18,921
This is a vow

1000
00:54:19,005 --> 00:54:21,048
to love and cherish each other

1001
00:54:21,549 --> 00:54:23,676
in sickness and in health

1002
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:26,471
in sadness and in joy

1003
00:54:26,763 --> 00:54:28,014
and in every circumstance.

1004
00:54:28,097 --> 00:54:32,602
Now, we will hear a wedding toast
from the bride's friend.

1005
00:54:33,144 --> 00:54:34,228
Here I go.

1006
00:54:48,493 --> 00:54:50,286
HELLO, I'M LEE UI-YEONG,
A FRIEND OF THE BRIDE, EUN-MI

1007
00:55:00,129 --> 00:55:01,255
Hello

1008
00:55:01,631 --> 00:55:04,008
I'm the friend's bride...

1009
00:55:07,053 --> 00:55:09,722
The bride's friend, Lee Ui-yeong.

1010
00:55:14,894 --> 00:55:17,355
I'm incredibly nervous right now

1011
00:55:18,105 --> 00:55:21,192
but I know the bride and the groom
standing in front of me

1012
00:55:21,275 --> 00:55:24,487
must be so much more nervous.

1013
00:55:24,987 --> 00:55:28,157
In fact, they might feel
like their lives will flip upside-down

1014
00:55:29,116 --> 00:55:34,038
by the time they leave the hall
after the wedding.

1015
00:55:34,330 --> 00:55:36,123
THIRD ACT COMPANY ACTOR MEETING

1016
00:55:36,207 --> 00:55:38,167
Take your time to read it, Ji-su.

1017
00:55:38,251 --> 00:55:39,252
Okay.

1018
00:55:39,669 --> 00:55:42,004
THIRD ACT COMPANY ACTOR CONTRACT

1019
00:55:42,463 --> 00:55:46,467
We become hesitant
before making a big choice

1020
00:55:46,968 --> 00:55:48,886
because we have no idea

1021
00:55:49,554 --> 00:55:51,347
where our choice today

1022
00:55:51,931 --> 00:55:53,683
will lead us to in the future.

1023
00:55:53,766 --> 00:55:56,269
ACTOR SHIN JI-SU

1024
00:56:05,820 --> 00:56:07,321
We don't know what doors will open

1025
00:56:08,155 --> 00:56:10,908
and what doors will close.

1026
00:56:12,410 --> 00:56:14,370
The previous scene is taking a bit longer.

1027
00:56:14,453 --> 00:56:17,415
We don't know what we'll see
at the end of it, either.

1028
00:56:18,249 --> 00:56:20,042
None of us know

1029
00:56:21,002 --> 00:56:22,670
until we try.

1030
00:56:24,755 --> 00:56:27,174
JEONG-A WAS INCREDIBLE ON THE SET.
I COULD FEEL HER FOCUS AND PASSION

1031
00:56:32,054 --> 00:56:34,098
We make endless calculations

1032
00:56:35,224 --> 00:56:37,643
to brace ourselves
for the craziness of life

1033
00:56:38,686 --> 00:56:40,855
wonder all the "what ifs"

1034
00:56:41,856 --> 00:56:45,818
and just hope for the best sometimes.

1035
00:56:52,491 --> 00:56:53,659
Boo!

1036
00:56:53,743 --> 00:56:57,413
But in the end, life seems to be a journey

1037
00:56:58,205 --> 00:57:02,460
of learning to go forward
amidst all the uncertainty.

1038
00:57:04,712 --> 00:57:08,549
Marriage seems to be the same.

1039
00:57:10,968 --> 00:57:15,306
Of course, your lives together
will not always be smooth.

1040
00:57:15,514 --> 00:57:18,559
You'll have as many sad days as happy ones

1041
00:57:18,643 --> 00:57:22,563
and sometimes, you'll face surprises.

1042
00:57:23,940 --> 00:57:25,358
But despite that

1043
00:57:26,442 --> 00:57:30,446
if you trust each other,
prepare yourselves to go through anything

1044
00:57:32,198 --> 00:57:36,911
and want to walk into the uncertain future
with each other

1045
00:57:37,161 --> 00:57:38,955
I'd like to wish the couple

1046
00:57:39,372 --> 00:57:43,793
nothing but the best until the end
as they courageously take on life.

1047
00:57:44,085 --> 00:57:46,462
Congratulations on getting married.

1048
00:57:59,183 --> 00:58:02,353
Groom and bride, march!

1049
00:58:03,229 --> 00:58:04,939
Please give them a big applause.

1050
00:58:45,855 --> 00:58:47,940
What a day it was, huh?

1051
00:58:48,024 --> 00:58:49,108
Yeah.

1052
00:58:49,442 --> 00:58:51,569
Seeing the bride laugh and cry

1053
00:58:51,944 --> 00:58:54,280
made me realize
how big of a deal getting married was.

1054
00:58:55,656 --> 00:58:59,577
I feel like I just saw
my child get married.

1055
00:59:03,831 --> 00:59:05,708
- You did well.
- Yeah.

1056
00:59:06,125 --> 00:59:08,502
Oh, you want to take a walk
before heading back?

1057
00:59:08,586 --> 00:59:09,587
Sure.

1058
00:59:10,129 --> 00:59:11,130
Here.

1059
00:59:16,385 --> 00:59:20,139
What did you write in the speech
that you prepared?

1060
00:59:20,431 --> 00:59:23,392
Oh, Eun-mi specifically asked me

1061
00:59:23,476 --> 00:59:25,227
not to make her cry.

1062
00:59:25,311 --> 00:59:26,312
I see.

1063
00:59:26,395 --> 00:59:28,606
So, I took a very statistical approach.

1064
00:59:29,732 --> 00:59:31,192
- You want to hear it?
- Yeah.

1065
00:59:31,776 --> 00:59:35,571
"Korea has 50 million people,
15 of which whom are single.

1066
00:59:35,905 --> 00:59:38,616
Half of them are men,
so, that's 7.5 million

1067
00:59:38,824 --> 00:59:42,078
and assuming only 90% are straight
that leaves 6.8 million.

1068
00:59:42,661 --> 00:59:46,957
So, what are the chances of you
falling in love with just one of them?"

1069
00:59:48,209 --> 00:59:50,169
- That's a very slim chance.
- Exactly.

1070
00:59:50,586 --> 00:59:51,879
That was my speech.

1071
00:59:52,713 --> 00:59:55,299
That it was a miracle
for them to meet and fall in love.

1072
01:00:00,221 --> 01:00:01,680
Oh, I have a present.

1073
01:00:02,223 --> 01:00:03,224
What is it?

1074
01:00:17,029 --> 01:00:18,114
It's beautiful.

1075
01:00:18,364 --> 01:00:21,408
I wanted to give you one
since the first time I met you.

1076
01:00:21,951 --> 01:00:24,912
It was a bit hard
to get your ring size, though.

1077
01:00:25,287 --> 01:00:27,832
How did you figure it out?

1078
01:00:31,210 --> 01:00:32,211
Thanks.

1079
01:00:33,337 --> 01:00:34,463
You want to go with me?

1080
01:00:34,672 --> 01:00:36,465
Yeah, take me!

1081
01:00:37,133 --> 01:00:38,926
Bring me to New York, too.

1082
01:00:39,927 --> 01:00:43,430
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

1083
01:00:47,852 --> 01:00:49,019
We drank so much.

1084
01:00:49,103 --> 01:00:50,312
This looks great.

1085
01:00:50,396 --> 01:00:52,231
- I love you, Ui-yeong!
- Me too!

1086
01:00:52,314 --> 01:00:53,357
Love you!

1087
01:00:54,108 --> 01:00:55,276
I love you, Chef!

1088
01:00:55,359 --> 01:00:56,402
Me too.

1089
01:00:57,236 --> 01:00:59,572
- You have to come back.
- I love you extra, Tae-seop!

1090
01:01:06,996 --> 01:01:08,122
Hello, sir.

1091
01:01:08,581 --> 01:01:09,582
Oh, hi!

1092
01:01:10,457 --> 01:01:12,877
- Did you finally get her ring size?
- Yeah.

1093
01:01:20,926 --> 01:01:22,261
That's her size.

1094
01:01:22,344 --> 01:01:24,680
Oh, this is her size?

1095
01:01:32,897 --> 01:01:34,481
Give me your hand. I'll put it on.

1096
01:01:52,291 --> 01:01:53,334
Is this it?

1097
01:01:56,420 --> 01:01:58,255
